PiperOrigin-RevId: 397252444
Change-Id: Ieff05360969026d211759d5687fad6d179bee64b","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Intel-tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/8894bcd76e8ba0e6c26553b118fff169dd5f8126"},{"sha":"3e8a7c649efeaf99cbd2726d48fe857562d4720f","author":{"name":"Ran Chen","email":"49043981742618ef538c755703712b0c26b8e5bf@google.com"},"message":"[retry]Fix a shape mismatch when partial batch handling is enabled

Partial batch handling will make the batch dimension unknown because of the
tf.cond(has_value, true_fn=get_value, false_fn=make_dummy). This tf.cond is
executed in DistributedIterator.get_next_as_optional() even when partial batch
handling is disabled. To counter this unnecessary shape lost, we recover the shape after tf.cond with the shape of the true branch. However we may recover it with the wrong shape when partial batch handling is enabled (as we could take the false branch).

This change refactors the partial batch handling logic so that
DistributedIterator.get_next() and DistributedIterator.get_next_as_optional()
is consistent.

The previous _get_next_as_optional is a misleading name as it does parial batch
handling and doesn't produce optional values. Hope that the picture is more
clear after this change.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 397252444
Change-Id: Ieff05360969026d211759d5687fad6d179bee64b","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mahak/tensorflow/commits/8894bcd76e8ba0e6c26553b118fff169dd5f8126"},{"sha":"3e8a7c649efeaf99cbd2726d48fe857562d4720f","author":{"name":"Ran Chen","email":"49043981742618ef538c755703712b0c26b8e5bf@google.com"},"message":"[retry]Fix a shape mismatch when partial batch handling is enabled

Partial batch handling will make the batch dimension unknown because of the
tf.cond(has_value, true_fn=get_value, false_fn=make_dummy). This tf.cond is
executed in DistributedIterator.get_next_as_optional() even when partial batch
handling is disabled. To counter this unnecessary shape lost, we recover the shape after tf.cond with the shape of the true branch. However we may recover it with the wrong shape when partial batch handling is enabled (as we could take the false branch).

This change refactors the partial batch handling logic so that
DistributedIterator.get_next() and DistributedIterator.get_next_as_optional()
is consistent.

The previous _get_next_as_optional is a misleading name as it does parial batch
handling and doesn't produce optional values. Hope that the picture is more
clear after this change.

Change-Id: Ic5bf5c08cd1c042ca6fa84f3164bc095d2d2c8a2","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/greedisgoood/tensorflow/commits/e01adf20a2cd46e786446c5e0956fd7b40d324ab"},{"sha":"03ba364effe173d0b185977f0c14a48863d1f277","author":{"name":"Reed Wanderman-Milne","email":"75734eae9db3e4fb4d6c671d22722b468d1a389b@google.com"},"message":"Make GPU scatter ND ops deterministic by running them on CPU.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 397252444
Change-Id: Ieff05360969026d211759d5687fad6d179bee64b","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/8894bcd76e8ba0e6c26553b118fff169dd5f8126"},{"sha":"3e8a7c649efeaf99cbd2726d48fe857562d4720f","author":{"name":"Ran Chen","email":"49043981742618ef538c755703712b0c26b8e5bf@google.com"},"message":"[retry]Fix a shape mismatch when partial batch handling is enabled

Partial batch handling will make the batch dimension unknown because of the
tf.cond(has_value, true_fn=get_value, false_fn=make_dummy). This tf.cond is
executed in DistributedIterator.get_next_as_optional() even when partial batch
handling is disabled. To counter this unnecessary shape lost, we recover the shape after tf.cond with the shape of the true branch. However we may recover it with the wrong shape when partial batch handling is enabled (as we could take the false branch).

This change refactors the partial batch handling logic so that
DistributedIterator.get_next() and DistributedIterator.get_next_as_optional()
is consistent.

The previous _get_next_as_optional is a misleading name as it does parial batch
handling and doesn't produce optional values. Hope that the picture is more
clear after this change.

The test has race condition, which is addressed by the patch.

The race is next:

    Master thread is calling execute (effectively blocked, waiting for
callback to be called)
    "Async" thread picks up the callback
    Call the callback
    Then sets the variables in test
    After call back is called, master thread is unblocked and may check
the variables (set in point 4 by the "async" thread) earlier then they
actually changed

Changes:

    callback should be called as the last step (after flag variables are
    set), as it effectively unblock the master thread

fixes #18974","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sturkmen72/opencv/commits/eb6d8e6af233e0c021bfae4e04f36b2b844157a8"},{"sha":"6f5af6eb42e2aef207d248882bd3fec2e3882208","author":{"name":"Alexander Alekhin","email":"68add3c7f0912f500ebe6e9539930fd1bb229c72@gmail.com"},"message":"Merge pull request #18982 from anton-potapov:sole_tbb_executor_async_test","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sturkmen72/opencv/commits/6f5af6eb42e2aef207d248882bd3fec2e3882208"},{"sha":"fc54853d44fae538a54b7d27f219bd24a57e0f4c","author":{"name":"Alexander Alekhin","email":"68add3c7f0912f500ebe6e9539930fd1bb229c72@gmail.com"},"message":"Merge pull request #18972 from Rightpoint:task/colejd/prevent-existing-xcframework-error","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sturkmen72/opencv/commits/fc54853d44fae538a54b7d27f219bd24a57e0f4c"}]

Change-Id: Ia5f62bbc2ad889be038a79fe17e6ddbf6ee4051c","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/clayne/tensorflow/commits/85d82f670f783c5345154ea5b919bcb0896e093b"},{"sha":"63290b0a36867f57b30a998dfc184617c0a78ff2","author":{"name":"Mehdi Amini","email":"808100943be7b7010123d78912f654820a5ee1c1@google.com"},"message":"Hook MLIR optimization into Grappler

After this change, we can start inserting passes written with MLIR TFG inside Grappler.
We will also start now to always round-trip between GraphDef and MLIR during Grappler
execution, ensuring this codepath is enabled by default.

Right now, libtensorflow_framework.so and pywrap_tensorflow_internal.so are
duplicating grappler, and so they are duplicating MLIR as well. There is a larger cleanup
needed to refactor all this and avoid this large code duplication between these libraries.
For now linker-scripts are hiding symbols to avoid collisions, in particular since MLIR has
some global registries and the "TypeID" mechanism which expects a unique address for
some symbols.

Re-apply the original change after fixing a few bugs this uncovered,
